# Wiki note standard

This is a hand-curated research brain (no engine, nothing auto-generated). Three note types:
`source` (`sources/{kind}/`), `concept` (`concepts/`), `moc` (`maps/`).

## Source credibility (papers)

Every `source_kind: paper` needs `tier`, `venue`, `year`, `authors`, `approx_citations`.

- **A** = top venue (NeurIPS/ICML/ICLR/Nature/Science) OR frontier lab (DeepMind, OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Meta FAIR) OR the canonical paper for a method.
- **B** = solid peer-reviewed, reasonably cited for its age.
- **C** = preprint/blog/unvetted — only with explicit justification. Never add tier-C silently; flag it.

## Typed linking (required)

Every source links ≥2 concepts and ≥1 sibling source. Every concept links ≥2 sources.
In `## Related`, state the relationship — don't drop a bare wikilink:

```markdown
## Related
- extends [[2018-lopez-scvi]] — adds semi-supervised labels on scVI's latent
- benchmarks [[2020-li-dr-benchmark]] — evaluated head-to-head there
```

Verbs: `extends`, `contradicts`, `benchmarks`, `supersedes`, `applies`, `introduces`, `background-for`.

## Frontmatter shape

Follow `docs/00-system/templates/source-note.md` and `concept-note.md`. Filenames:
papers `{year}-{author}-{short-slug}.md`; discussions `{date}-{seq}-{slug}.md`. Wikilinks use
the filename stem only. Tags stay in the small taxonomy (`#source`/`#concept`/`#moc`,
`domain/*`, `topic/*`, `method/*`, `field/*`) — don't invent one-offs.

## Don't

- No `runs/`, `engine`, or `regenerate_cmd` fields — that machinery was removed.
- Don't web-search to fill gaps in a note's *claims*; ground claims in the source itself.
